CGTN's "A Decade of Change" series recounts the remarkable changes in Chinese provinces, municipalities and autonomous regions over the past 10 years. This episode features central China's Hunan Province. Located in the middle reaches of the Yangtze watershed, it borders the province-level divisions of Hubei to the north, Jiangxi to the east, Guangdong and Guangxi to the south, Guizhou to the west and Chongqing to the northwest.